						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 961, Pramāthi, Vaiśākha, Saṅkrānti,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1039, April 23,</hi> Vṛishabha-saṅkarānti, and mentions the <hi rend="bold">Noḻamba</hi> chief <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalla-Noaḷambapallava-Permānaḍidēva</hi> as ruling over <hi rend="bold">Kōgaḷi five-hundred, Kadambaḷi thousand,</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Pergaḍe</hi> <hi rend="bold">Bāchimayya</hi> as administering <hi rend="bold">Kañchikeṟe.</hi> It records that the <hi rend="italic">Sandhivigrahi</hi> <hi rend="bold">Aridāsayya</hi> set up a <hi rend="italic">liṅga</hi> and granted some land for its worship.</p>						

						</summary>
